    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>High-angular resolution dust polarization of proto-brown dwarf harbouring core - L328 SMM2</prj:name>
        <prj:note>High-angular resolution observations of polarised dust emission can put constraints on the theoretical models available currently to explain collapse of dense cores. The observational characteristics that are particularly of interest are (a) the magnetic eld pattern within 4000 AU of the central source (b) the relative orientation between the outflow from the L328-IRS and the mean polarization position angle. The strength of the magnetic field evaluated from the observed polarization emission could provide vital information on the role played by the magnetic fields in mediating the collapse, in particular in L328 SMM2, to form a sub-stellar object.</prj:note>
