        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Adopting a peak intensity of 0.2 mJy within 2000 beam estimated by Lee et. al. 2009 towards L328-IRS the peak intensity expected from 2.3 arcsec aperture in 870 micron is 3 mJy. To detect a polarization of 5% , the peak polarization intensity is expected to be 20 micronJy per polarization component. With an angular resolution of 2.3 arcsec, we will be probing magnetic fields at a spatial resolution of 506 AU in L328 SMM2. Using the online time estimation calculator, with a sensitivity requirement of 20 micronJy, the estimated integration time is 3.94 hours.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
